<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-11-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-11-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="358" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d358">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4757/26.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Chargé <persName type="to">Schuyler</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-11-09"><hi rend="italic">November 9,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 72.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose a copy of a letter<note n="a" xml:id="d358fna">Not printed.</note> from Mr. Charles L. Magee,
                            secretary of the American National Red Cross., who asks that it may <pb facs="1130" n="980" xml:id="pg_980"/> be ascertained whether the
                            Russian Red Cross Society is still engaged in relief work in behalf of
                            the famine sufferers and, if so, whether a further contribution, already
                            on, deposit here, would be acceptable.</p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">E. Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>